Betrayed										KEY:Drawback ~ Betrayed								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Drawback																																																																						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Drawback ~ Betrayed],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Drawback]																																																																DESC:You were reported to a dangerous authority and narrowly escaped death. You second-guess your instincts constantly, leaving you never sure whether or not to trust someone and endangered if you encounter that group's agents again. You can roll twice and take the lower result on Sense Motive checks to get hunches. You cannot reroll this result, even if you have another ability that would normally allow you to do so.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.6
Empty Mask										KEY:Drawback ~ Empty Mask							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Drawback																																																																						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Drawback ~ Empty Mask],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Drawback]																																																															DESC:You have spent so long hiding your true identity to escape political enemies that you have lost much of your sense of self. You take a –1 penalty on Will saving throws against compulsions. This penalty increases to –2 against foes who know your true identity.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.7	ASPECT:SaveBonus|-1 on saves vs. compulsions (-2 if the caster knows your true identity)
Guilty Fraud									KEY:Drawback ~ Guilty Fraud							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Drawback																																																																						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Drawback ~ Guilty Fraud],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Drawback]																																																															DESC:You received something through trickery that you did not deserve, and your guilt for the misdeed distracts you from dangers around you. You take a –4 penalty on Bluff checks against creatures with an attitude toward you of indifferent or better.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.7
Infamous										KEY:Drawback ~ Infamous								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Drawback																																																																						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Drawback ~ Infamous],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Drawback]																																																																DESC:You were publicly linked, truthfully or not, to a crime of significant infamy. You draw attention wherever you go and risk imprisonment or worse in the jurisdiction where the crime was committed. You and your apparent allies take a –4 penalty on Diplomacy checks to interact with law-abiding citizens (except enemies of the authority that accused you).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																							BONUS:SITUATION|Diplomacy=Influence law-abiding citizens|-4																															COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.7
Information Overload								KEY:Drawback ~ Information Overload						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Drawback																																																																						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Drawback ~ Information Overload],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Drawback]																																																														DESC:You have had access to thousands of spy reports, many of which turned out to be based on faulty deductions or even intentionally false stories spread by opposed spy groups. At this point, you have been exposed to false knowledge as much as accurate information, and you can't always remember which is which. You take a –2 penalty on all Knowledge checks, and if you fail a Knowledge check by 5 or more, you can recall information that is diametrically opposed to the truth.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											BONUS:SKILL|TYPE=Knowledge|-2											COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.7
Lonely										KEY:Drawback ~ Lonely								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Drawback																																																																						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Drawback ~ Lonely],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Drawback]																																																																DESC:You are far too easily convinced of the friendly intentions of others. You take a –2 penalty on Sense Motive checks and on Perception checks to see through disguises, and on saving throws against charm spells and spell-like abilities.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										BONUS:SITUATION|Perception=See Through Disguise|-2																	BONUS:SKILL|Sense Motive|-2											COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.7	ASPECT:SaveBonus|-2 on saves vs. charm spells and spell-like abilities
Magical Klutz									KEY:Drawback ~ Magical Klutz							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Drawback																																																																						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Drawback ~ Magical Klutz],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Drawback]																																																															DESC:You were born in a place with a plethora of strangely interacting magic and magic is dangerously eager to surge into action around you. You roll twice and take the lower result on Use Magic Device checks to activate items blindly and on Reflex saving throws against effects produced by magic items.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.7
Occult Bargain									KEY:Drawback ~ Occult Bargain							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Drawback																																																																						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Drawback ~ Occult Bargain],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Drawback]																																					PRESPELLTYPE:2,ANY=0,ANY=1																						DESC:You draw magical power from a source, such as a mysterious eidolon, shame-filled phantom, or First World patron, who insists that its identity remains secret. You take a –1 penalty on concentration checks, and you must invoke the entity's name by word or text each day or be unable to regain spell slots that day. You must be able to cast 0-level and 1st-level spells as a class feature to select this drawback.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.7
Righteous Indignation								KEY:Drawback ~ Righteous Indignation					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Drawback																																																																						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Drawback ~ Righteous Indignation],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Drawback]																																																														DESC:You have difficulty controlling your temper after living in inhuman conditions. Whenever a foe provokes an attack of opportunity from you, you must take it unless you succeed at a Will save against a DC %1. You take a –1 penalty on Will saving throws against spells with the emotion descriptor that do not also have the fear descriptor.|10+TL																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.7
Secret Shame									KEY:Drawback ~ Secret Shame							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Drawback																																																																						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Drawback ~ Secret Shame],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Drawback]																																																															DESC:You have a terrible fear of the public at large, a group, or an important person (such as your order of knights, your liege lord, your family, or your lover) learning a shameful truth about you. You take a –1 penalty on saving throws against fear effects, and the DC of any Intimidate check to demoralize you is reduced by 1. If you would normally be immune to fear, you do not take these penalties, but instead lose your immunity to fear (regardless of its source).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.7	ASPECT:SaveBonus|-1 on saves vs. fear effects
Too Many Secrets									KEY:Drawback ~ Too Many Secrets						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Drawback																																																																						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Drawback ~ Too Many Secrets],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Drawback]																																																														DESC:You've told too many lies, and made up too many cover stories, and now even you can't keep it all straight. The lies have become reality to you, which makes it difficult to think of a new convincing lie. You hesitate at crucial moments when trying to fool those around you, and likely shouldn't be in the field at all anymore. You take a –2 penalty on Bluff checks and saving throws against illusions.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																							BONUS:SKILL|Bluff|-2												COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.7	ASPECT:SaveBonus|-2 on saves vs. illusions
Vainglory										KEY:Drawback ~ Vainglory							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Drawback																																																																						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Drawback ~ Vainglory],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Drawback]																																																																DESC:You compulsively seek recognition for your deeds, making it hard to act with subtlety. You take a –1 penalty on Bluff, Disguise, and Stealth checks, and the save DC of any illusion you create is 1 lower than normal.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								BONUS:DC|SCHOOL.Illusion|-1																										BONUS:SKILL|Bluff|-1												COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.7

