One of Those Faces								KEY:Rogue Talent ~ One of Those Faces					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RogueClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.SpellLike.RogueTalent																																																																																																																																																		DESC:Each day, you can use disguise self as a spell-like ability for up to %1 minutes. This duration need not be continuous, but it must be used in 10-minute increments. Additionally, once you have used this ability, whenever you use it for the next 24 hours you must take the same alternate appearance.|TL*10																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.21
Scrying Familiarity								KEY:Rogue Talent ~ Scrying Familiarity					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RogueClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.RogueTalent																																																																																																																																																		DESC:You are well acquainted with scrying sensors. You can roll twice and take the better result on saving throws against divination (scrying) spells and effects, on Perception checks to notice scrying sensors, and on caster level checks to overcome spell resistance when you use a scrying spell or effect. If you notice a magical sensor, you can attempt a Stealth check opposed by the caster's caster level check to avoid being detected by the sensor.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.23

One of Those Faces								KEY:Investigator ~ One of Those Faces					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:InvestigatorTalent.SpecialQuality.SpellLike								PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Narrows Survivor,Trait ~ Wealthy Dabbler,Trait ~ Brute,Trait ~ Failed Apprentice,Trait ~ Militia Veteran,Trait ~ Rapscallion,Trait ~ River Rat,Trait ~ Vagabond Child,Trait ~ Well Informed																																																																																																						DESC:Each day, you can use disguise self as a spell-like ability for up to %1 minutes. This duration need not be continuous, but it must be used in 10-minute increments. Additionally, once you have used this ability, whenever you use it for the next 24 hours you must take the same alternate appearance.|TL*10																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.21
Scrying Familiarity								KEY:Investigator ~ Scrying Familiarity					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:InvestigatorTalent.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																																																																																																																																																				DESC:You are well acquainted with scrying sensors. You can roll twice and take the better result on saving throws against divination (scrying) spells and effects, on Perception checks to notice scrying sensors, and on caster level checks to overcome spell resistance when you use a scrying spell or effect. If you notice a magical sensor, you can attempt a Stealth check opposed by the caster's caster level check to avoid being detected by the sensor.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.23

One of Those Faces								KEY:Slayer Talent ~ One of Those Faces					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SlayerTalent.LesserSlayerTalent.Slayer Class Feature.SpecialQuality.SpellLike			PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Narrows Survivor,Trait ~ Wealthy Dabbler,Trait ~ Brute,Trait ~ Failed Apprentice,Trait ~ Militia Veteran,Trait ~ Rapscallion,Trait ~ River Rat,Trait ~ Vagabond Child,Trait ~ Well Informed																																																																																																						DESC:Each day, you can use disguise self as a spell-like ability for up to %1 minutes. This duration need not be continuous, but it must be used in 10-minute increments. Additionally, once you have used this ability, whenever you use it for the next 24 hours you must take the same alternate appearance.|TL*10																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.21
Scrying Familiarity								KEY:Slayer Talent ~ Scrying Familiarity					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SlayerTalent.LesserSlayerTalent.Slayer Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																																																																																																																																														DESC:You are well acquainted with scrying sensors. You can roll twice and take the better result on saving throws against divination (scrying) spells and effects, on Perception checks to notice scrying sensors, and on caster level checks to overcome spell resistance when you use a scrying spell or effect. If you notice a magical sensor, you can attempt a Stealth check opposed by the caster's caster level check to avoid being detected by the sensor.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.23

