Concealed Strike									KEY:Vigilante Talent ~ Concealed Strike					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Vigilante Talent.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																																															!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Vigilante Talent ~ Concealed Strike																																																																				PREVARGTEQ:VigilanteTalentLVL,6																DESC:Whenever the vigilante attacks an opponent with a concealed weapon that his target wasn't aware of, he can attempt a Bluff check to feint that opponent as a move action. If he has the Improved Feint feat, he attempts this check as a free action instead.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.27
Fantastic Stride									KEY:Vigilante Talent ~ Fantastic Stride					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Vigilante Talent.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																																															!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Vigilante Talent ~ Fantastic Stride																																																																				PREVARGTEQ:VigilanteTalentLVL,6																DESC:The vigilante gains Spring Attack as a bonus feat, ignoring its prerequisites. At 10th level and every 4 levels thereafter, the vigilante can designate one additional creature when he uses Spring Attack. The vigilante's movement this round does not provoke attacks of opportunity from any of these secondary creatures.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														ABILITY:FEAT|VIRTUAL|Spring Attack																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.27
Major Magic										KEY:Vigilante Talent ~ Major Magic						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Vigilante Talent.SpecialQuality.SpellLike									PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Vigilante Talent ~ Minor Magic																												!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Vigilante Talent ~ Major Magic																																																																					PREVARGTEQ:VigilanteTalentLVL,4																DESC:[NOT IMPLEMENTED] A vigilante with this talent gains the ability to cast a 1st-level spell drawn from the same spell list as the minor magic talent. The vigilante can cast this spell %1/day as a spell-like ability. The caster level for this ability is equal to the vigilante's level. The save DC for this spell is equal to 10 + the vigilante's Intelligence modifier (for psychic, sorcerer/wizard, and witch spells), Wisdom (for cleric, druid, and shaman spells), or Charisma (for bard spells). A vigilante must have a score of at least 11 in the appropriate ability to select this talent.|VigilanteTalentLVL/4																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.27
Minor Magic										KEY:Vigilante Talent ~ Minor Magic						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Vigilante Talent.SpecialQuality.SpellLike																																																!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Vigilante Talent ~ Minor Magic																																																																																										DESC:[NOT IMPLEMENTED] A vigilante with this talent selects one of the following spells lists: bard, cleric, druid, psychic, shaman, sorcerer/wizard, or witch. Once this decision is made, the selection cannot be changed. The vigilante gains the ability to cast a 0-level spell from the selected spell list. This spell can be cast two times per day as a spell-like ability. The caster level for this ability is equal to the vigilante's level. The save DC for this spell is equal to 10 + the vigilante's Intelligence modifier (for psychic, sorcerer/wizard, and witch spells), Wisdom (for cleric, druid, and shaman spells), or Charisma (for bard spells).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.27
Mockery										KEY:Vigilante Talent ~ Mockery						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Vigilante Talent.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																																															!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Vigilante Talent ~ Mockery																																																																																											DESC:The vigilante gains Antagonize as a bonus feat. He can target a creature with the Intimidate version of Antagonize twice each day, rather than just once.	DESC:The effects of the Intimidate version of Antagonize last a number of rounds equal to the vigilante's Charisma modifier (minimum 1).|max(1,CHA)|PERVARGTEQ:VigilanteTalentLVL,12																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											ABILITY:FEAT|VIRTUAL|Antagonize																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.27
Shadow Tricks									KEY:Vigilante Talent ~ Shadow Tricks					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Vigilante Talent.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary								PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Archetype,Vigilante Archetype ~ Teisatsu																													!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Vigilante Talent ~ Shadow Tricks																																																																																										DESC:The teisatsu gains a single ninja trick (but not a master trick) of his choice. He cannot select a rogue talent in place of a ninja trick in this manner. If he selects a ninja trick marked with an asterisk (*), that talent applies to his hidden strikes instead of to sneak attacks, and the talent counts as a stalker vigilante talent with an asterisk (*) for the limitation of applying only one effect to a single hidden strike.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Ninja Trick|1																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.26
Team Player										KEY:Vigilante Talent ~ Team Player						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Vigilante Talent.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																																															!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Vigilante Talent ~ Team Player																																																																																										DESC:The vigilante gains Swift Aid as a bonus feat, ignoring its prerequisites. Additionally, the vigilante can choose to use the feat as a standard action, in which case it applies to every ally adjacent to the vigilante.	DESC:He can increase the bonus provided to one ally by this feat to +2 by using the aid another action as a move action rather than a swift action.|PREVARGTEQ:VigilanteTalentLVL,10																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																ABILITY:FEAT|VIRTUAL|Swift Aid																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.27
Take 'Em Alive									KEY:Vigilante Talent ~ Take 'Em Alive					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Vigilante Talent.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																																															!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Vigilante Talent ~ Take 'Em Alive																																																																																									DESC:The vigilante doesn't take the usual –4 penalty on attack rolls made to deal nonlethal damage with weapons that normally deal lethal damage. In addition, the vigilante gains a +%1 bonus on all attack and damage rolls for attacks that deal only nonlethal damage and have no secondary effects (such as poison).|min(5,(VigilanteTalentLVL+1)/3)																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.27
